# SCG Ideogram4 Prompt Agent — AI provider configuration
#
# Copy this file to ".env" in the same directory and fill in your keys.
# Keys live ONLY on the server (this file). They are never sent to the browser;
# the UI talks to providers through a server-side proxy.
#
# One provider per line:
#   AI_PROVIDER_<ID> = Label | model | base_url (blank = official OpenAI) | api_key
#
# • Comment a line out to hide that provider from the UI.
# • Add as many as you like (any unique <ID>).
# • After editing this file, click "Refresh" next to the provider picker in the
#   UI to reload it live — no restart needed.
#
# AI_PROVIDER_OPENAI = OpenAI (gpt-5.4-mini) | gpt-5.4-mini |  | {key}
# AI_PROVIDER_GROK   = grok-4.3 | grok-4.3 | https://api.x.ai/v1 | {key}
# AI_PROVIDER_GEMINI = Gemini 3.5 Flash | gemini-3.5-flash | https://generativelanguage.googleapis.com/v1beta/openai | {key}
#
# Gemini via Vertex AI (Vertex-only keys/projects). Authenticates with Google
# OAuth, NOT a static key: it uses Application Default Credentials (run
# `gcloud auth application-default login`) unless you point the 4th field at a
# service-account JSON. Requires the `google-auth` package (see requirements.txt).
# Format: Label | model | vertex://PROJECT/LOCATION | [sa.json]
# Use "global" as the LOCATION for the global endpoint, or a region like us-central1.
# AI_PROVIDER_VERTEX = Gemini · Vertex | gemini-3.5-flash | vertex://your-gcp-project/us-central1 |
AI_PROVIDER_LOCAL  = Local (qwen3.6-35b) | qwen3.6-35b-a3b-uncensored-hauhaucs-aggressive | http://192.168.0.180:1234 | 123
